comments: Beasley (UTA) and Reid (MIN) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Reid (MIN) briefly grasps Agbaji's (UTA) jersey as they engage for off ball positioning.
Rivers (MIN) and Conley (UTA) come together at the same spot in the air and marginal contact occurs as Conley secures the rebound.
Kessler (UTA) is already in Edwards' (MIN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Reid (MIN) jumps forward into Agbaji's (UTA) space and initiates arm contact that affects his shot near the rim.
Anderson (MIN) is already in Agbaji's (UTA) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Rivers (MIN) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Rivers (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball at the end of Clarkson's (UTA) drive to the basket.
Clarkson's (UTA) left foot lands out of bounds while he is still in possession of the ball.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: As Edwards (MIN) attempts to pass the ball, Rivers (MIN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Kessler (UTA) is already in Edwards' (MIN) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Rivers (MIN) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Clarkson (UTA) is bracing for the contact from Rivers (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as Clarkson releases from the contact.
Rivers (MIN) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
As part of his fade away shooting motion, Clarkson (UTA) brings his leg towards Rivers (MIN) and marginal lower body contact occurs as Rivers contest the jump shot.
Russell (MIN) briefly grasps Kessler's (UTA) arm and marginal contact occurs as the long rebound bounces away from their matchup.
Kessler (UTA) is already in Rivers' (MIN) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

As Rivers (MIN)  moves towards Clarkson's (UTA) space, Clarkson's forearm makes some contact with Rivers' head as he moves towards the ball.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Rivers (MIN) turns into Clarkson's (UTA) path and delivers body to body contact that affects his SQBR.
Kessler (UTA) legally contests McDaniels' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
